CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778105470
OL,3,CExperts discover potential cause for
OL,4,Cstroke affecting 35,000 people in the
OL,5,CUK
OL,7,FResearchers have pinpointed the
OL,8,Fpotential cause of a type of stroke
OL,9,Fsuffered by about 35,000 people in the
OL,10,FUK every year, which could explain why
OL,11,Fwidely used treatments do not work.
OL,13,FThis discovery could help pave the way
OL,14,Ffor new treatments for lacunar
OL,15,Fstrokes, which are caused by damage to
OL,16,Fthe tiny blood vessels deep within the
OL,17,Fbrain. This type of stroke can lead to
OL,18,Fpeople developing problems with
OL,19,Fthinking, memory, movement, and
OL,20,Fultimately dementia.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
