FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778105470
OL,3,CExperts discover potential cause for
OL,4,Cstroke affecting 35,000 people in the
OL,5,CUK
OL,7,FThis could explain why usual
OL,8,Ftreatments, such as anti-platelet
OL,9,Fdrugs, which stop blood clots from
OL,10,Fforming in the arteries, do not work,
OL,11,Fresearchers said.
OL,13,FElsewhere, widened arteries were also
OL,14,Flinked to a higher risk of having so-
OL,15,Fcalled silent strokes, which happen
OL,16,Fwithout obvious symptoms. More than
OL,17,Fone in four patients had silent
OL,18,Fstrokes during the study despite
OL,19,Fhaving treatment to help prevent
OL,20,Ffurther strokes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
