PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778105470
OL,3,CExperts discover potential cause for
OL,4,Cstroke affecting 35,000 people in the
OL,5,CUK
OL,7,FThe British Heart Foundation estimates
OL,8,Fthat lacunar strokes account for about
OL,9,Fa fifth of all strokes in the UK, or
OL,10,Fabout 35,000 every year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778105470
OL,3,CExperts discover potential cause for
OL,4,Cstroke affecting 35,000 people in the
OL,5,CUK
OL,7,FExperts have called for new treatments
OL,8,Fto target the underlying damage to the
OL,9,Fsmall blood vessels in the brain.
OL,10,FJoanna Wardlaw, professor of applied
OL,11,Fneuroimaging at the University of
OL,12,FEdinburgh's Institute for Neuroscience
OL,13,Fand Cardiovascular Disease and group
OL,14,Fleader at the UK Dementia Research
OL,15,FInstitute, said: "This study provides
OL,16,Fstrong evidence that lacunar stroke is
OL,17,Fnot caused by fatty blockage of larger
OL,18,Farteries, but by disease of the small
OL,19,Fvessels within the brain itself."
OL,26,@wD@ROU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
